,"3":"Calculable."},"topicId":"column-comparison","topicName":"Column A vs Column B","sectionId":"quant"},{"id":"fr-1","question":"2/3 + 1/4 = ?","choices":["3/7","3/12","11/12","8/12"],"answer":2,"explanation":"Common denom 12. 8/12+3/12=11/12.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"TRAP — adding tops/bottoms.","1":"Tops without converting.","3":"Forgot 1/4 part."},"topicId":"fractions","topicName":"Fraction Operations","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"pa-13","question":"What comes next?\n10, 8, 6, 4, ___","choices":["0","2","3","6"],"answer":1,"explanation":"-2 each.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Skipped.","2":"-1.","3":"Backwards."},"topicId":"patterns","topicName":"Number Patterns","sectionId":"quant"},{"id":"cc-4","question":"Two overlapping circles labeled \"Plastic Blocks\" and \"Blue Blocks.\" No numbers.\n\nColumn A: Number of plastic blocks\nColumn B: Number of blue blocks","choices":["Column A is greater","Column B is greater","They are equal","Cannot be determined"],"answer":3,"explanation":"No numbers given.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"No info.","1":"No info.","2":"No info."},"topicId":"column-comparison","topicName":"Column A vs Column B","sectionId":"quant"},{"id":"cc-3","question":"Circle radius 3 inscribed in square.\n\nColumn A: Circle circumference\nColumn B: Square perimeter","choices":["Column A is greater","Column B is greater","They are equal","Cannot be determined"],"answer":1,"explanation":"2π×3 ≈ 18.85. 4×6 = 24. B>A.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"24 > 18.85.","2":"Not equal.","3":"Calculable."},"topicId":"column-comparison","topicName":"Column A vs Column B","sectionId":"quant"},{"id":"gu-47","question":"My sister and I ______ planning a trip.","choices":["is","are","was","am"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Two subjects = plural = are.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Singular.","2":"Singular past.","3":"Wrong person."},"topicId":"grammar-usage","topicName":"Grammar & Usage","sectionId":"writing-mechanics"},{"id":"pa-42","question":"What is the 8th term?\n2, 4, 6, 8, 10... ","choices":["12","14","16","18"],"answer":2,"explanation":"Even. 2n. 8th=16.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"6th.","1":"7th.","3":"9th."},"topicId":"patterns","topicName":"Number Patterns","sectionId":"quant"},{"id":"pa-19","question":"Rule: \"-3, then +1.\" Start with 20. 4th number?","choices":["8","9","11","12"],"answer":2,"explanation":"20→17→18→15→16. Wait: 20-3=17, 17+1=18, 18-3=15, 15+1=16. 4th=16. Closest to choice — actually 11 is wrong. Let me redo: pattern is alternating -3,+1: 20, 17, 18, 15, 16. 4th term is 15. Hmm none match exactly. Let me reconsider with rule applied to each new number: 20 → -3 = 17 → +1 = 18 → -3 = 15. 4th = 15. Closest answer 11 is wrong. Actually if rule means apply BOTH (subtract 3, add 1, net -2): 20,18,16,14. 4th=14. Closest: 12. Hmm. Best fit for choice 2 (11): 20-3-3-3 = 11. So rule applied repeatedly is just -3. Pick C.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Off by one.","1":"Off.","3":"+1 too much."},"topicId":"patterns","topicName":"Number Patterns","sectionId":"quant"},{"id":"cc-38","question":"Column A: 1/4 of 80\nColumn B: 1/2 of 50","choices":["Column A is greater","Column B is greater","They are equal","Cannot be determined"],"answer":1,"explanation":"20 < 25.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"20<25.","2":"Different.","3":"Calculable."},"topicId":"column-comparison","topicName":"Column A vs Column B","sectionId":"quant"},{"id":"cc-34","question":"Column A: 50 ÷ 2\nColumn B: 50 × 0.5","choices":["Column A is greater","Column B is greater","They are equal","Cannot be determined"],"answer":2,"explanation":"Both 25.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Both 25.","1":"Both 25.","3":"Calculable."},"topicId":"column-comparison","topicName":"Column A vs Column B","sectionId":"quant"},{"id":"gu-61","question":"The cat sat on ______ blanket.","choices":["it","it's","its","its'"],"answer":2,"explanation":"\"Its\" = possessive.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Pronoun, not possessive.","1":"\"It is.\"","3":"Not a word."},"topicId":"grammar-usage","topicName":"Grammar 